    "description": "Streptokinase is an enzyme derived from beta-hemolytic streptococci, used as a medication to dissolve blood clots in various medical conditions, particularly in acute myocardial infarction (heart attack) and pulmonary embolism. It works by converting plasminogen to plasmin, which then breaks down fibrin in clots, effectively restoring blood flow to affected areas.",
    "uses": "Streptokinase is primarily utilized in emergency settings for the treatment of acute myocardial infarction, where it helps to quickly dissolve clots in coronary arteries, potentially reducing heart damage and improving survival rates. Additionally, it is employed in cases of pulmonary embolism, where it aids in dissolving blood clots in the lungs, alleviating symptoms and preventing complications such as respiratory distress. Its use can also extend to treating deep vein thrombosis and other thromboembolic conditions, depending on the clinical situation and the patient's health status.",
